# Gerotech — multi-agent sync (Cursor + Cline)

This repo is edited in **Cursor** and **VS Code (Cline)**. Stay aligned via git + shared files.

## Every session — read first

1. `.clinerules` — live session state, blockers, recent decisions
2. `JOURNAL.md` — newest entry first
3. `git log -5 --oneline`

Also useful: `AGENTS.md`, `design-spec.md`, `cline-project-handoff.md`

## Every session — write before ending

1. Prepend a short entry to `JOURNAL.md` (date, agent, what changed, loose ends)
2. Update **Current Session State** in `.clinerules` (last updated, active agent, last commit)

## Code conventions (do not drift)

- Static HTML/CSS/JS only — no frameworks or build tools
- CSS order: `tokens.css` → `components.css` → `layout.css`
- Navigo font kit `lqh7ybe` — weights **400 and 700 only**
- BEM classes; brand colors only in `tokens.css`
- Unsplash placeholders OK; never guess open client decisions

## Local preview

Run **Tasks: Run Task → Serve Gerotech (8080)** or `python3 -m http.server 8080` from repo root.

## Figma

Paste a frame/layer link with `node-id`. Use `get_design_context`, then adapt to this project's HTML/BEM/tokens — not React/Tailwind verbatim.
